You are helping build Billcraft — a freelancer invoice generator and manager web app.

## Project Context
- Read PROJECT_SPEC.md at the project root for the full product specification
- This includes database schema, screen specs, design tokens, folder structure, and build sequence
- Always reference the spec before generating code — don't invent features or patterns not in the spec

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14+ (App Router) with TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui for components
- Supabase for database, auth, and file storage
- @react-pdf/renderer for invoice PDFs
- Resend for sending emails
- Deployed on Vercel

## Code Style Rules
- Use TypeScript strictly — no `any` types
- Use server components by default, add "use client" only when needed (interactive components)
- Use Supabase server client in server components, browser client in client components
- All database queries should go through server actions or API routes, never directly in client components
- Use the app router conventions: page.tsx for pages, layout.tsx for layouts, loading.tsx for loading states
- Component files use PascalCase (e.g., MetricCards.tsx)
- Utility files use camelCase (e.g., formatCurrency.ts)
- Follow the folder structure defined in PROJECT_SPEC.md Section 8

## UI/Design Rules
- Use shadcn/ui components as the base — don't build custom components when shadcn has one
- Follow the design tokens in PROJECT_SPEC.md Section 10 for colors, spacing, and typography
- Brand color is #534AB7 (purple) — used for primary buttons, links, and accents
- Status badge colors: Draft=gray, Sent=blue, Viewed=amber, Overdue=red, Paid=green
- Keep the UI minimal and clean — freelancers want speed, not decoration
- Mobile responsiveness is required but desktop-first for now

## Database Rules
- All tables have Row Level Security (RLS) enabled
- Every query must respect user_id scoping — never fetch data without filtering by the authenticated user
- Use Supabase's generated types from the database schema
- Payment details are stored as JSONB for flexibility

## When Asked to Build Something
1. Check if it's defined in PROJECT_SPEC.md
2. Follow the spec exactly for structure and behavior
3. Use the design tokens for styling
4. Handle loading states and errors
5. Make it work first, make it pretty second

## When You Don't Know Something
- Say so clearly rather than guessing
- Suggest checking the relevant documentation (Next.js docs, Supabase docs, shadcn/ui docs)
- Never generate code that you're uncertain about without flagging the uncertainty

## Common Patterns in This Project
- Currency formatting: Always use Intl.NumberFormat for currency display
- Date formatting: Use date-fns library, display short format like "Mar 14"
- Invoice numbers: Auto-generated as "{prefix}-{number}" padded to 4 digits (e.g., INV-0042)
- Empty states: Every list/table should have a meaningful empty state with a CTA
- Toast notifications: Use sonner (via shadcn) for success/error feedback
